# Core Commands

## Quality Gates (MANDATORY)

```bash
bun run lint                   # Catches common errors
bun run test                   # Unit and component tests
bun run ci                     # MANDATORY before PR
bun run typecheck              # If present in package.json
```

## Standard Commands

### /code-review

- Use `code-reviewer` agent
- For contracts: also use `solidity-auditor`
- Focus: quality, architecture, security

### /debug

1. Reproduce issue
2. Gather context
3. Analyze logs
4. Test fix
5. Verify no regressions

### /test

```bash
bun run test                   # Unit tests
bun run test:integration       # Integration tests
bun run ci                     # Full test suite
```

### /pr

1. Ensure CI green (`bun run ci`)
2. Semantic commits: `type(scope): description`
3. Create PR from feature branch
4. Link Linear issue if applicable

### /setup

Configure MCP servers:

- Linear (issues)
- Context7 (docs)
- DeepWiki (repos)
- Sentry (errors)
- Playwright (browser)
- Gemini (AI)
- OpenZeppelin (contracts)

## Critical Rules

- ALWAYS run from repo root
- Use `bun run test` NOT `bun test`
- CI must pass before PR
